com.bluegosling.collections

Class Immutables

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.collections.Immutables

  • public final class Immutables
extends Object
    Utility methods for creating immutable collections and maps and for viewing immutable collections and maps using the standard JCF collection and map interfaces. Standard collection and map views of immutable collections and maps throw UnsupportedOperationException from all mutation methods.

    • Method Detail

      • asIfMutable

        public static <E> Collection<E> asIfMutable(ImmutableCollection<? extends E> collection)
        Returns a view of the given immutable collection as a standard Collection. The returned collection is a view, not a copy, so it is inexpensive to create. But since the input collection is immutable, the returned collection is indistinguishable from a snapshot. The returned collection throws UnsupportedOperationException for every operation that would otherwise mutate the collection.
        Parameters:
        collection - an immutable collection
        Returns:
        a view of the given collection via the standard Collection interface

      • cast

        public static <E,S extends ImmutableCollection<? extends E>,T extends ImmutableCollection<E>> T cast(S collection)
        Safely upcasts the element type of an immutable collection. This operation is safe thanks to the input being immutable. This can help adapt instances of immutable collection to otherwise invariant collection types, without the need for unchecked casts.
        Type Parameters:
        E - the element type of the collection
        S - the source type of the collection being re-cast
        T - the target type to which the collection is re-cast
        Parameters:
        collection - an immutable collection
        Returns:
        the input collection, but with its element type re-cast
